The paper proposes a method for shape complementarity analysis that applies to objects of arbitrary shape, which suggests a focus on computer graphics (cs.GR) and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions applications in assembly automation and robot motion planning, which are related to robotics (cs.RO). The mention of micro- and nano-fabrication suggests a possible connection to multimedia (cs.MM), and the mention of protein-ligand binding and rational drug design suggests a possible connection to machine learning (cs.LG).
